<TITLE> Malaysia won't take in 55000 workers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 11 (bdnews24.com)  One of the major importers of Bangladeshi workers, Malaysia will not take in 55000 Bangladeshi workers in the face of global economic recession, the expatriates welfare minister said Wednesday. "The Malaysian government on Tuesday confirmed that they would not take in any more workers now," Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain said at the Secretariat after a meeting with his ministry's officials on the Malaysian decision. Not only Malaysia, other countries have also stopped importing workers due to global economic meltdown, he said. Mosharraf said the government has launched diplomatic initiatives to stop Malaysia sending workers back home and arrange alternate jobs them. Asked what effects the Malaysian decision may have on Bangladesh economy, the minister said, "Foreign currency inflow will definitely reduce if workers are not sent out or are forced to come back." bd
